answers.answer: I didn't have that.  What did your doctor say about it?

My midwife said my body is using fat stores instead of using my carb intake. So that means i have an insulin problem aks gestational diabetes or i just didnt eat enough the day before aka starved myself. I had eaten just not sugar and carbs bc it was the day before my glucose test

Ketones usually show up in urine when you are ingesting a lot of protein and vegetables too. If you don't eat a lot of carbs and sugar your body could just be utilizing everything you do ingest. It's not totally uncommon, I wouldn't be too concerned unless you actually did test positive for gestational diabetes.

title: 27 weeks ketones
